'''[[first]] [[declension]]'''

# In Latin, a group of nouns declined (inflected) in the same way, which have an ''-a-'' in their stems.

: Most first declension nouns are feminine, but a few like ''[[agricola]]'' and ''[[nauta]]'' are masculine.

